quran[51]{c,v,t}:
  52,24,"Around them will be youthfulness, like pearls well guarded"
  52,25,"They will advance each other, engaging in mutual inquiry"
  52,26,"They will say, “Before, we were not without fear, because of our people"
  52,27,"“But God has been good to us, and has delivered us from the penalty of the scorching wind"
  52,28,"“Indeed we used to call on Him. Truly it is He, the Merciful Benefactor, the Merciful Redeemer.”"
  52,29,"Therefore proclaim His praises, for by the grace of your Lord, you are no oracle, nor are you one possessed"
  52,30,Or do they call you a poet? We await them with calamity in due time.”
  52,31,"Say, “Wait, I too will wait with you.”"
  52,32,"Is it that their mind leads them to this, or are they just a people transgressing beyond bounds"
  52,33,"Or do they say, “He fabricated the message?” No, they have no faith"
  52,34,"Let them produce a hadith like it, if they speak the truth"
  52,35,"Were they created of nothing, or did they create themselves"
  52,36,"Or did they create the heavens and the earth? No, they have no firm beliefs"
  52,37,"Or are the treasures of your Lord with them, or are they the managers"
  52,38,"Or have they a ladder, by which they can listen? Then let such a listener produce clear proof"
  52,39,Or has He only daughters and you have sons
  52,40,"Or is it that you ask for a reward, so that they are burdened with a load of debt"
  52,41,"Or is the unknown in their hands, and they write it down"
  52,42,Or do they plot and scheme? But those who defy God are themselves the subject of a plan
  52,43,"Or do they have a god other than God. Exalted is God, far above the things they associate with Him"
  52,44,"If they saw a piece of the sky falling, they would say, “Fog-clouds gathered in heaps.”"
  52,45,"So leave them alone until they encounter that day of theirs, when they will faint"
  52,46,"The day when their plotting will not avail them, and no help will be given to them"
  52,47,"And indeed, for those who do wrong, there is another punishment besides this, but most of them do not understand"
  52,48,"Now wait in patience, the command of your Lord, for indeed you are in Our Eyes, and glorify your Lord with praise while you stand forth"
  52,49,"And for part of the night praise Him, and at the retreat of the stars"
  53,1,By the star when it goes down
  53,2,Your companion is neither astray nor being misled
  53,3,Nor does he say anything of his own volition
  53,4,It is no less than inspiration sent down to him
  53,5,He was taught by one mighty in power
  53,6,"Endued with wisdom, for he appeared"
  53,7,While he was in the highest part of the horizon
  53,8,Then he approached and came closer
  53,9,And was at a distance of only two bow-lengths or nearer
  53,10,So God conveyed the inspiration to His servant which He meant to convey
  53,11,His heart in no way falsified that which he saw
  53,12,Will you then dispute with him concerning what he saw
  53,13,For indeed he saw him at a second descent
  53,14,Near the lotus-tree beyond which none may pass
  53,15,Near is the garden of abode
  53,16,"Behold, the lotus-tree was shrouded"
  53,17,"His sight never deviated, nor did it go wrong"
  53,18,"For truly he saw the signs of his Lord, the Greatest"
  53,19,Have you seen Lat and ‘Uzza
  53,20,"And another, the third, Manat"
  53,21,"What, for you the male, and for Him, the female"
  53,22,"Behold, that would indeed be a division unfair"
  53,23,"These are nothing but names which you have made up, you and your fathers, for which God has sent down no authority. They follow nothing but speculation, and what their own soul’s desire. Even though there has already come to them guidance from their Lord"
  53,24,"No, will human beings have everything they pursue"
  53,25,But it is to God that the end and the beginning belong